title: AE2 CraftingJob Redstone Output
content:
local CONFIG = {
	pollInterval = 1.0,
	redstoneSide = "top",
	watchlistFile = "watchlist.txt",
	logFile = "patters.log",
	enableLogging = true,
}

local lastCpuSnapshot = nil

local watchlist = {}

local function log(msg)
	print(msg)

	if CONFIG.enableLogging then
		local file = fs.open(CONFIG.logFile, "a")
		if file then
			file.write(msg .. "\n")
			file.close()
		end
	end
end

local function logColored(msg, color)
	if term.isColor() then
		term.setTextColor(color)
		print(msg)
		term.setTextColor(colors.white)
	else
		print(msg)
	end

	if CONFIG.enableLogging then
		local file = fs.open(CONFIG.logFile, "a")
		if file then
			file.write(msg .. "\n")
			file.close()
		end
	end
end

local function drawLine(y, color)
	if term.isColor() then
		term.setTextColor(color)
		term.setCursorPos(1, y)
		term.write(string.rep("=", term.getSize()))
		term.setTextColor(colors.white)
	end
end

local function drawBox(x, y, width, height, title, color)
	if term.isColor() then
		term.setTextColor(color)

		-- Draw top border
		term.setCursorPos(x, y)
		term.write("+" .. string.rep("-", width - 2) .. "+")

		-- Draw title line
		if title then
			term.setCursorPos(x, y + 1)
			term.write("| " .. title .. string.rep(" ", width - #title - 3) .. "|")
		end

		-- Draw middle lines
		for i = 2, height - 1 do
			if not title or i > 1 then
				term.setCursorPos(x, y + i)
				term.write("|" .. string.rep(" ", width - 2) .. "|")
			end
		end

		-- Draw bottom border
		term.setCursorPos(x, y + height)
		term.write("+" .. string.rep("-", width - 2) .. "+")

		term.setTextColor(colors.white)
	end
end

-- Clear screen and show header
local function showHeader()
	if term.isColor() then
		term.clear()
		local termWidth, _ = term.getSize()
		local title = "PATTERN DETECTOR"
		local titleX = math.floor((termWidth - #title) / 2) + 1

		term.setCursorPos(1, 1)
		term.setBackgroundColor(colors.blue)
		term.setTextColor(colors.white)
		term.write(string.rep(" ", termWidth))
		term.setCursorPos(titleX, 1)
		term.write(title)
		term.setBackgroundColor(colors.black)
		term.setTextColor(colors.white)
	end
end

local function showStatusBar(redstoneOn)
	if term.isColor() then
		local termWidth, _ = term.getSize()
		local statusOn = "Redstone Lamp: ON"
		local statusOff = "Redstone Lamp: OFF"
		local status = redstoneOn and statusOn or statusOff
		local color = redstoneOn and colors.green or colors.gray

		local barY = 5
		term.setCursorPos(1, barY)
		term.setBackgroundColor(colors.black)
		term.write(string.rep(" ", termWidth))

		-- Center the status text
		local barX = math.floor((termWidth - #status) / 2) + 1
		term.setCursorPos(barX, barY)
		term.setTextColor(color)
		term.write(status)
		term.setTextColor(colors.white)
	end
end

-- Show watchlist: "Watchlist:"
local function showWatchlist()
	if term.isColor() then
		local y = 7
		local termWidth, _ = term.getSize()
		local label = "Watchlist:"
		local names = {}
		for i, item in ipairs(watchlist) do
			table.insert(names, item.displayName)
		end
		local namesStr = (#watchlist == 0) and "(empty)" or table.concat(names, ", ")
		-- Compose the full line
		local line = label .. " " .. namesStr
		-- Truncate if too long
		if #line > termWidth then
			local maxNamesLen = termWidth - #label - 4
			if maxNamesLen < 0 then
				maxNamesLen = 0
			end
			namesStr = namesStr:sub(1, maxNamesLen) .. "..."
			line = label .. " " .. namesStr
		end
		-- Clear the line
		term.setCursorPos(1, y)
		term.setBackgroundColor(colors.black)
		term.write(string.rep(" ", termWidth))
		-- Write the label in cyan, then the names in white/orange
		term.setCursorPos(1, y)
		term.setTextColor(colors.cyan)
		term.write(label)
		term.setTextColor(#watchlist == 0 and colors.orange or colors.white)
		term.write(" " .. namesStr)
		term.setTextColor(colors.white)
	else
		if #watchlist == 0 then
			log("Watchlist: (empty)")
		else
			local names = {}
			for i, item in ipairs(watchlist) do
				table.insert(names, item.displayName)
			end
			log("Watchlist: " .. table.concat(names, ", "))
		end
	end
end

-- Show crafting status
local function showCraftingStatus(craftingPatterns)
	if term.isColor() then
		local termWidth, _ = term.getSize()
		local title = "CRAFTING STATUS"
		local y = 9

		-- Calculate how many lines we need to clear
		local linesNeeded = 1 + math.max(1, #craftingPatterns)

		-- Clear the area
		for i = 0, linesNeeded do
			term.setCursorPos(1, y + i)
			term.setBackgroundColor(colors.black)
			term.write(string.rep(" ", termWidth))
		end

		-- Center and print the title
		local titleX = math.floor((termWidth - #title) / 2) + 1
		term.setCursorPos(titleX, y)
		term.setTextColor(colors.cyan)
		term.write(title)
		term.setTextColor(colors.white)

		if #craftingPatterns > 0 then
			local craftingLines = {}
			local maxLineLen = 0
			for i, crafting in ipairs(craftingPatterns) do
				local line = "+ "
					.. crafting.displayName
					.. " x"
					.. crafting.quantity
					.. " (CPU "
					.. crafting.cpuId
					.. ")"
				if #line > termWidth then
					line = line:sub(1, termWidth - 3) .. "..."
				end
				craftingLines[i] = line
				if #line > maxLineLen then
					maxLineLen = #line
				end
			end
			local blockWidth = maxLineLen
			local blockX = math.floor((termWidth - blockWidth) / 2) + 1
			for i, line in ipairs(craftingLines) do
				term.setCursorPos(blockX, y + i)
				term.setTextColor(colors.green)
				term.write(line)
				term.setTextColor(colors.white)
			end
		else
			local msg = "- No watchlisted items being crafted"
			if #msg > termWidth then
				msg = msg:sub(1, termWidth - 3) .. "..."
			end
			local msgX = math.floor((termWidth - #msg) / 2) + 1
			term.setCursorPos(msgX, y + 1)
			term.setTextColor(colors.orange)
			term.write(msg)
			term.setTextColor(colors.white)
		end
	else
		log("CRAFTING STATUS:")
		if #craftingPatterns > 0 then
			for _, crafting in ipairs(craftingPatterns) do
				log(" " .. crafting.displayName .. " x" .. crafting.quantity .. " (CPU " .. crafting.cpuId .. ")")
			end
		else
			log("- No watchlisted items being crafted")
		end
	end
end

-- Load watchlist from file
local function loadWatchlist()
	local items = {}

	if fs.exists(CONFIG.watchlistFile) then
		local file = fs.open(CONFIG.watchlistFile, "r")
		if file then
			local line = file.readLine()
			while line do
				local trimmed = line:gsub("^%s*(.-)%s*$", "%1")
				if trimmed ~= "" and not trimmed:match("^#") then
					table.insert(items, {
						name = trimmed,
						displayName = trimmed:gsub("minecraft:", ""):gsub("ftbmaterials:", ""),
					})
				end
				line = file.readLine()
			end
			file.close()
		end
	end

	-- Create default watchlist if empty
	if #items == 0 then
		items = {
			{ name = "minecraft:stone", displayName = "Stone" },
			{ name = "minecraft:iron_ingot", displayName = "Iron Ingot" },
		}

		-- Create watchlist file
		local file = fs.open(CONFIG.watchlistFile, "w")
		if file then
			for _, item in ipairs(items) do
				file.write(item.name .. "\n")
			end
			file.close()
		end
	end

	return items
end

-- Handle user input
local function handleUserInput()
	local input = read()
	if not input then
		return false
	end

	input = input:lower():gsub("^%s*(.-)%s*$", "%1")
end

-- Find ME Bridge
local function findMeBridge()
	if peripheral.isPresent("bottom") then
		local bridge = peripheral.wrap("bottom")
		if bridge and bridge.getCraftingCPUs then
			return bridge
		end
	end

	-- Try other sides
	for _, side in ipairs({ "left", "right", "front", "back", "top" }) do
		if peripheral.isPresent(side) then
			local bridge = peripheral.wrap(side)
			if bridge and bridge.getCraftingCPUs then
				return bridge
			end
		end
	end

	return nil
end

-- Take a snapshot of current CPU status with crafting job details
local function takeCpuSnapshot(bridge)
	local snapshot = {}

	if bridge.getCraftingCPUs then
		local success, cpus = pcall(bridge.getCraftingCPUs, bridge)
		if success and cpus then
			for i, cpu in ipairs(cpus) do
				snapshot[i] = {
					isBusy = cpu.isBusy,
					name = cpu.name,
					storage = cpu.storage,
					craftingJob = cpu.craftingJob,
				}
			end
		end
	end

	return snapshot
end

-- Check if any monitored patterns are being crafted
local function checkCraftingPatterns(bridge)
	local craftingPatterns = {}

	-- Take current snapshot
	local currentCpuSnapshot = takeCpuSnapshot(bridge)

	-- Check if any CPUs are busy
	local anyBusyCPUs = false
	for cpuId, cpu in pairs(currentCpuSnapshot) do
		if cpu.isBusy then
			anyBusyCPUs = true
		end
	end

	if not anyBusyCPUs then
		lastCpuSnapshot = currentCpuSnapshot
		return craftingPatterns
	end

	-- Analyze CPU changes based off previous snapshot
	if lastCpuSnapshot then
		-- Extract current crafting information
		for cpuId, currentCpu in pairs(currentCpuSnapshot) do
			if currentCpu.isBusy and currentCpu.craftingJob then
				local job = currentCpu.craftingJob
				if job.resource and job.resource.name then
					-- Check if this item is in watchlist
					for _, watchlistItem in ipairs(watchlist) do
						if job.resource.name == watchlistItem.name then
							table.insert(craftingPatterns, {
								pattern = watchlistItem,
								cpuId = cpuId,
								cpuName = currentCpu.name,
								quantity = job.quantity,
								displayName = job.resource.displayName or job.resource.name,
							})
							break
						end
					end
				end
			end
		end
	end

	lastCpuSnapshot = currentCpuSnapshot

	return craftingPatterns
end

-- Control redstone lamp
local function setRedstoneLamp(on)
	if on then
		redstone.setOutput(CONFIG.redstoneSide, true)
	else
		redstone.setOutput(CONFIG.redstoneSide, false)
	end
end

local function runMonitor()
	showHeader()
	watchlist = loadWatchlist()

	local bridge = findMeBridge()
	if not bridge then
		logColored("ERROR: No ME Bridge found!", colors.red)
		return
	end

	local lastState = false
	local controlMode = false

	while true do
		if controlMode then
			if handleUserInput() then
				sleep(0.1)
			else
				controlMode = false
				showHeader()
			end
		else
			if term.isColor() then
				local timer = os.startTimer(2)
				local event, param = os.pullEvent()

				if event == "timer" and param == timer then
				elseif event == "char" and param == "\r" then
					controlMode = true
				end
			end

			local craftingPatterns = checkCraftingPatterns(bridge)

			local currentState = #craftingPatterns > 0

			if currentState ~= lastState then
				setRedstoneLamp(currentState)
				lastState = currentState
			end

			showStatusBar(currentState)
			showWatchlist()
			showCraftingStatus(craftingPatterns)

			sleep(CONFIG.pollInterval)
		end
	end
end

runMonitor()

title: shell_install.ps1
content:
<# =======================
  Windows Terminal Pro Stack (no WSL)
  - Windows Terminal
  - PowerShell 7 (default)
  - Git + Git Bash profile
  - oh-my-posh + posh-git + PSReadLine
  - Nerd Font (Cascadia Code NF)
  - Pretty prompt (Powerlevel10k-style)
======================== #>

$ErrorActionPreference = 'Stop'

function Install-WingetPackage {
  param(
    [Parameter(Mandatory)] [string] $Id
  )
  Write-Host ">> Installing $Id via winget..." -ForegroundColor Cyan
  winget install --id $Id --silent --accept-source-agreements --accept-package-agreements | Out-Null
}

# 1) Base apps
Install-WingetPackage Microsoft.WindowsTerminal
Install-WingetPackage Microsoft.PowerShell
Install-WingetPackage Git.Git
Install-WingetPackage JanDeDobbeleer.OhMyPosh
Install-WingetPackage NerdFonts.CascadiaCode
# Скачивает и ставит Cascadia Code Nerd Font (Regular + Bold + Italic)
Invoke-WebRequest -Uri "https://github.com/ryanoasis/nerd-fonts/releases/latest/download/CascadiaCode.zip" -OutFile "$env:TEMP\CascadiaCode.zip"
Expand-Archive "$env:TEMP\CascadiaCode.zip" -DestinationPath "$env:TEMP\CascadiaCodeNF" -Force
Get-ChildItem "$env:TEMP\CascadiaCodeNF" -Filter "*.ttf" | ForEach-Object { $_.FullName | ForEach-Object { Write-Host "Installing font: $_"; Copy-Item $_ "$env:WINDIR\Fonts\" -Force } }


# Paths
$PwshPath = "${env:ProgramFiles}\PowerShell\7\pwsh.exe"
if (-not (Test-Path $PwshPath)) {
  # Sometimes installed per-user
  $PwshPath = "${env:LocalAppData}\Microsoft\PowerShell\pwsh.exe"
}
if (-not (Test-Path $PwshPath)) {
  throw "PowerShell 7 (pwsh.exe) not found after install."
}

# 2) PS modules (install into PowerShell 7 scope)
$moduleInstallCmd = @'
Install-Module posh-git -Scope CurrentUser -Force
Install-Module PSReadLine -Scope CurrentUser -Force -SkipPublisherCheck
'@

& $PwshPath -NoProfile -NoLogo -Command $moduleInstallCmd

# 3) PowerShell profile setup (pretty prompt with oh-my-posh)
$ProfilePath = & $PwshPath -NoLogo -NoProfile -Command '$PROFILE'
$ProfileDir  = Split-Path $ProfilePath -Parent
if (-not (Test-Path $ProfileDir)) { New-Item -ItemType Directory -Path $ProfileDir -Force | Out-Null }

# oh-my-posh themes path (winget EXE install)
$PoshThemes = Join-Path $env:LOCALAPPDATA 'Programs\oh-my-posh\themes'
$ThemeFile  = Join-Path $PoshThemes 'powerlevel10k_modern.omp.json'
if (-not (Test-Path $ThemeFile)) {
  # fallback
  $ThemeFile = Join-Path $PoshThemes 'jandedobbeleer.omp.json'
}

$ProfileContent = @"
# ---------- Pro Prompt ----------
Import-Module posh-git
Import-Module PSReadLine

# Oh My Posh init (needs EXE installed by winget)
oh-my-posh init pwsh --config "$ThemeFile" | Invoke-Expression

# PSReadLine: history & suggestions
Set-PSReadLineOption -EditMode Windows
Set-PSReadLineOption -PredictionSource History
Set-PSReadLineOption -PredictionViewStyle ListView

# QoL
Set-Alias reload '& `$PROFILE'
"@

Set-Content -Path $ProfilePath -Value $ProfileContent -Encoding UTF8
Write-Host ">> PowerShell profile configured at: $ProfilePath" -ForegroundColor Green

# 4) Windows Terminal settings patch (set pwsh default, add Git Bash profile, set Nerd Font)
# Detect settings.json location(s)
$WTSettingsCandidates = @(
  (Join-Path $env:LOCALAPPDATA 'Packages\Microsoft.WindowsTerminal_8wekyb3d8bbwe\LocalState\settings.json'),
  (Join-Path $env:LOCALAPPDATA 'Microsoft\Windows Terminal\settings.json')
) | Where-Object { $_ -ne $null }

$WTSettings = $WTSettingsCandidates | Where-Object { Test-Path $_ } | Select-Object -First 1

if (-not $WTSettings) {
  # Create minimal settings.json if missing (Store app usually generates it on first run)
  $FallbackDir = Join-Path $env:LOCALAPPDATA 'Microsoft\Windows Terminal'
  if (-not (Test-Path $FallbackDir)) { New-Item -ItemType Directory -Path $FallbackDir -Force | Out-Null }
  $WTSettings = Join-Path $FallbackDir 'settings.json'
  '{ "profiles": { "list": [] } }' | Set-Content -Path $WTSettings -Encoding UTF8
}

Write-Host ">> Patching Windows Terminal settings: $WTSettings" -ForegroundColor Cyan

# Load JSON safely
$raw = Get-Content $WTSettings -Raw
try { $json = $raw | ConvertFrom-Json -ErrorAction Stop } catch {
  throw "Cannot parse Windows Terminal settings.json. Open once and save settings from UI, then rerun."
}

if (-not $json.profiles) { $json | Add-Member -NotePropertyName profiles -NotePropertyValue (@{}) }
if (-not $json.profiles.list) { $json.profiles.list = @() }

function Set-Or-AddProperty {
  param(
    [Parameter(Mandatory)] $Object,
    [Parameter(Mandatory)] [string] $Name,
    [Parameter()] $Value
  )
  if ($null -ne $Object.PSObject.Properties[$Name]) {
    $Object.$Name = $Value
  } else {
    $Object | Add-Member -NotePropertyName $Name -NotePropertyValue $Value -Force
  }
}

function Ensure-Profile {
  param(
    [Parameter(Mandatory)][string] $Name,
    [Parameter(Mandatory)][string] $Cmd,
    [Parameter()][string] $Args,
    [Parameter()][string] $FontFace = 'Cascadia Code NF',
    [Parameter()][string] $Icon
  )

  # Найдём существующий профиль по имени
  $existing = $json.profiles.list | Where-Object { $_.name -eq $Name } | Select-Object -First 1

  $cmdline = if ($Args) { "$Cmd $Args" } else { $Cmd }

  if (-not $existing) {
    # Создаём новый профиль
    $existing = [pscustomobject]@{
      guid             = ([guid]::NewGuid()).ToString("B")
      name             = $Name
      commandline      = $cmdline
      startingDirectory= $null
      hidden           = $false
      font             = @{ face = $FontFace }
    }
    if ($Icon) { $existing | Add-Member -NotePropertyName icon -NotePropertyValue $Icon }
    $json.profiles.list += $existing
  } else {
    # Обновляем/добавляем свойства безопасно
    Set-Or-AddProperty -Object $existing -Name 'commandline' -Value $cmdline
    Set-Or-AddProperty -Object $existing -Name 'hidden' -Value $false

    # font: может отсутствовать или быть простым строковым полем в старых схемах
    if ($null -eq $existing.PSObject.Properties['font'] -or $existing.font -isnot [object]) {
      Set-Or-AddProperty -Object $existing -Name 'font' -Value (@{ face = $FontFace })
    } else {
      Set-Or-AddProperty -Object $existing.font -Name 'face' -Value $FontFace
    }

    if ($Icon) { Set-Or-AddProperty -Object $existing -Name 'icon' -Value $Icon }
  }

  return $existing
}

# Ensure PowerShell 7 profile (default)
$pwshProf = Ensure-Profile -Name 'PowerShell 7' -Cmd $PwshPath -Args '' -FontFace 'Cascadia Code NF' -Icon ''
# Ensure Git Bash profile
$GitBash = 'C:\Program Files\Git\bin\bash.exe'
$gitIcon = 'C:\Program Files\Git\mingw64\share\git\git-for-windows.ico'
$gitArgs = '--login -i'
$gitProf = $null
if (Test-Path $GitBash) {
	$iconPath = if (Test-Path $gitIcon) { $gitIcon } else { $null }
	$gitProf = Ensure-Profile -Name 'Git Bash' -Cmd $GitBash -Args $gitArgs -FontFace 'Cascadia Code NF' -Icon $iconPath
}

# Set default profile to PowerShell 7
$json.defaultProfile = $pwshProf.guid

# Save JSON (preserve formatting reasonably)
($json | ConvertTo-Json -Depth 10) | Set-Content -Path $WTSettings -Encoding UTF8

Write-Host "`n✅ Done. Please restart Windows Terminal." -ForegroundColor Green
Write-Host "   PowerShell 7 is the default profile with a pretty Git-aware prompt."
Write-Host "   Font set to: Cascadia Code Nerd Font"
Write-Host "   Extra profile added: Git Bash" -ForegroundColor DarkGray

content:
#!/usr/bin/env bash
DEBUG=0 # set to 1 for dry running with stdout verbosity
        # will still populate INTERFOLDER

        ### README
    ## DEPENDENCIES
# ffmpeg
# libheif-examples
# renrot
# INSTALL VIA apt install ffmpeg libheif-examples renrot -y

#################################################################
### START OF CONFIG #############################################

        ### CONFIG OF FOLDERS
# tmp folder
INTERFOLDER="~/.mediatmp"
# drop folder, if not specified FULL PATH in SECOND parameter
DROPFOLDER="~/Videos/transcode/in"
# out folder, can be specified FULL PATH by FIRST parameter
OUTFOLDER="~/Videos/transcode/out"

        ### CONFIG OF FFMPEG (OBLIGATORY)

    ## VIDEOS
# minimum byte-size (not kB/MB/GB!) of file to process (smaller will be skipped)
SMALLVID=0
# api for scaling. "scale" if on CPU, "scale_vaapi" if on GPU via VAAPI, check documentation for other apis scaling hook
VIDSCALEAPI="scale_vaapi"
# video target bitrate. you can use e.g. "512k" or "4M"
VIDEOBITS="4M"
# target size in pixels on LONGER side
VIDEOSIZE=1920
# main function to tune
VIDFFMPEG() {
    ffmpeg -hide_banner \
        -hwaccel vaapi -hwaccel_output_format vaapi \
        -i "$v" $VF \
        -c:v hevc_vaapi \
        -extbrc 1  -look_ahead_depth 40 \
        -b:v "$VIDEOBITS" \
        -c:a copy \
        "$OUTFOLDER/$VIDNEWNAME.mp4"
    }

    ## IMAGES
# api for scaling. "scale" if on CPU, "scale_vaapi" if on GPU via VAAPI, check documentation for other apis scaling hook
PICSCALEAPI="scale"
# quality factor - lower is better (i.e. bigger byte-size)
IMAGECRF=22
# target size in pixels on SHORTER side
IMAGESIZE=2000
# main function to tune
PICFFMPEG() {
    ffmpeg -hide_banner -i "$i" $VF \
        -c:v libaom-av1 -crf "$IMAGECRF" \
        -cpu-used 0 "$OUTFOLDER/${i%.*}.avif"
    }


##### OPTIONAL config below #####################################

        ### FILETYPE ARRAYS
    ## generally no need to change that.
# "good" are usually well-compressed to begin with and will be COPIED
goodVariant=( "avif" "AVIF" "webp" "WEBP" )
# ffmpeg chokes on HEIF, thus conversion out of that format
heifVariant=( "heic" "heif" "HEIC" "HEIF" )
# jpegs, due to poor renrot compatibility
jpegVariant=( "jpeg" "jpg" "JPEG" "JPG" )
# the rest, compatible with ffmpeg
otherVariant=( "jxl" "JXL" "tif" "tiff" "TIF" "TIFF" "png" "PNG" "bmp" "BMP" )
# videos
vidVariant=( "mov" "MOV" "mp4" "MP4" "mkv" "MKV" )

### END OF CONFIG ###############################################
#################################################################



# PREP
if [[ ! -d "$INTERFOLDER" ]]; then mkdir -p "$INTERFOLDER" ; fi
if [[ ! -z $1 ]]; then OUTFOLDER="$1" ; fi
if [[ ! -z $2 ]]; then DROPFOLDER="$2" ; fi

if [[ `ls "$DROPFOLDER" | wc -c` -eq 0 ]]; then
    echo "Drop folder empty or absent. (Be sure to use FULL PATHs, or tilde expansion.)"
    exit
fi
shopt -s extglob

# DEFINE FUNCTIONS
function IMAGETRANSCODE {
    VIDDATA=`ffprobe "$i" 2>&1 | grep Video:`
    if [[ $VIDDATA =~ ([0-9]{3,4})x([0-9]{3,4}) ]]; then
        width="${BASH_REMATCH[1]}"
        height="${BASH_REMATCH[2]}"

    # SET UP SIZING
        #check if vertical
        if [[ $width -le $IMAGESIZE ]] && [[ $height -le $IMAGESIZE ]]; then
            test $DEBUG = 1 && echo "# resizing $i not necessary"
            VF=""
        else
            if [[ $height -gt $width ]]; then   # vertical aspect
                VF="-vf $PICSCALEAPI=$IMAGESIZE:-2"
            else                                # horizontal aspect
                VF="-vf $PICSCALEAPI=-2:$IMAGESIZE"
            fi
        fi

        if [[ $DEBUG = 1 ]]; then echo "FFMPEG $i with res '$VF'"
        else
            PICFFMPEG || echo "$i crashed ffmpeg!" >> "$DROPFOLDER/.errors.log"
        fi

    else # error logging
        if [[ ${i:0:1} -ne "*" ]]; then
            if [[ $DEBUG = 1 ]]; then echo "# resolution of $i failed to be established"
            else
                echo "$i couldn't be processed." >> "$DROPFOLDER/.errors.log"
            fi
        fi
    fi
    }

function VIDEOTRANSCODE {
    VIDDATA=`ffprobe "$v" 2>&1 | grep Video:`

    # Read MOV metadata from iPhones
    if [[ ${v:0:4} -eq "IMG_" ]]; then
        test $DEBUG = 1 && echo "# renaming $v"
        VIDSTAMP=`ffprobe "$v" 2>&1 | grep com.apple.quicktime.creationdate | cut -c39-`
        if [[ -z $VIDSTAMP ]]; then
            test $DEBUG = 1 && echo "# unable to find creationdate"
            VIDNEWNAME="${v%.*}"
        else
            VIDNEWNAME="${VIDSTAMP:0:4}${VIDSTAMP:5:2}${VIDSTAMP:8:2}_${VIDSTAMP:11:2}${VIDSTAMP:14:2}${VIDSTAMP:17:2}"
            echo "Renaming $v to $VIDNEWNAME.mp4."
        fi
    else
        VIDNEWNAME="${v%.*}"
    fi

    # determine scale
    if [[ $VIDDATA =~ ([0-9]{3,4})x([0-9]{3,4}) ]]; then
        width="${BASH_REMATCH[1]}"
        height="${BASH_REMATCH[2]}"

        if [[ $width -le $VIDEOSIZE ]] && [[ $height -le $VIDEOSIZE ]]; then
            test $DEBUG = 1 && echo "# resizing $v not necessary"
            VF=""
        else
            if [[ $height -gt $width ]]; then   # vertical aspect
                VF="-vf $VIDSCALEAPI=-2:$VIDEOSIZE"
            else                                # horizontal aspect
                VF="-vf $VIDSCALEAPI=$VIDEOSIZE:-2"
            fi
        fi

        if [[ $DEBUG = 1 ]]; then echo "FFMPEG $v with res '$VF' and new name $VIDNEWNAME"
        else
            VIDFFMPEG || echo "$v crashed ffmpeg!" >> "$DROPFOLDER/.errors.log"
        fi

    else # error logging
        if [[ ${v:0:1} -ne "*" ]]; then
            if [[ $DEBUG = 1 ]]; then echo "# resolution of $v failed to be established"
            else
                echo "$v couldn't be processed." >> "$DROPFOLDER/.errors.log"
            fi
        fi
    fi
    }



                cd "$DROPFOLDER"
        ### START ACTUAL WORK
    ## copy good images without processing
test $DEBUG = 1 && echo "### START ###"
for img in "${goodVariant[@]}" ; do
    test $DEBUG = 1 && echo "# copying $img files"
    cp *.$img "$OUTFOLDER/"
done

    ## HEVC imgs convert
for heimg in "${heifVariant[@]}"; do
    for h in *.$heimg ; do
        test $DEBUG = 1 && echo "# converting HEIC $h"
        heif-convert -q 100 "$h" "$INTERFOLDER/$h.jpg"
    done
done

    ## copy images to actually transcode
for jpimg in "${jpegVariant[@]}" "${otherVariant[@]}" ; do
    cp *.$jpimg "$INTERFOLDER/"
done




                cd "$INTERFOLDER"
        ### WORK ON PICTURES
    ## rename files
for n in !([0-9][0-9][0-9][0-9][0-9][0-9][0-9][0-9]_[0-9][0-9][0-9][0-9][0-9][0-9]*) ; do
# jpegs via renrot
    if [[ ${jpegVariant[@]} =~ ${n##*.} ]]; then
        test $DEBUG = 1 && echo "# attempting renrot of $n"
        renrot -n %Y%m%d_%H%M%S "$n"
    fi # TODO: some universal FFPROBE&REGEX method of doing that not just for JPEGs
done

    ## transcode all
for i in * ; do
    test $DEBUG = 1 && echo "# function image transcode $i"
    IMAGETRANSCODE
done

    ## cleanup
rm "$INTERFOLDER/"*



                cd "$DROPFOLDER"
    ## VIDEOS
for vid in "${vidVariant[@]}" ; do
    for v in *.$vid ; do

# if small file then not worth it
        SIZE=`stat "$v" | grep Size: | cut -c9-19`
        if [[ $SIZE -le $SMALLVID ]]; then
            if [[ $DEBUG -eq 1 ]]; then echo "# just moving $v (small size)"
            else cp "$v" "$OUTFOLDER/"
            fi

        else
            test $DEBUG = 1 && echo "# function video transcode $v"
            VIDEOTRANSCODE
        fi
    done
done

echo "### FINISHED ###"

#!/usr/bin/env bash
set -euo pipefail

TIMESTAMP=$(date +%Y%m%d-%H%M%S)
SSHD="/etc/ssh/sshd_config"
BACKUP="${SSHD}.backup.${TIMESTAMP}"
REVERT_SCRIPT="/root/sshd_config_revert_${TIMESTAMP}.sh"
FALLBACK_USER="recovery"

if [ "$(id -u)" -ne 0 ]; then
  echo "Script harus dijalankan sebagai root atau via sudo. Mengulangi dengan sudo..."
  exec sudo bash "$0" "$@"
fi

echo "=== Backup konfigurasi SSH ke: $BACKUP ==="
cp -a "$SSHD" "$BACKUP" || { echo "Gagal backup $SSHD"; exit 1; }

# minta password root
while true; do
  read -s -p "Masukkan password baru untuk root: " ROOTPW
  echo
  read -s -p "Konfirmasi password root: " ROOTPW2
  echo
  [ "$ROOTPW" = "$ROOTPW2" ] && break
  echo "Password tidak cocok — coba lagi."
done

# juga buat fallback user untuk mencegah terkunci
if id "$FALLBACK_USER" >/dev/null 2>&1; then
  echo "User fallback '$FALLBACK_USER' sudah ada. Tidak akan dibuat ulang."
  USE_FALLBACK=false
else
  USE_FALLBACK=true
  echo "Membuat user fallback: $FALLBACK_USER (dengan password yang sama seperti root)"
fi

# tulis revert script (agar mudah kembali)
cat > "$REVERT_SCRIPT" <<EOF
#!/usr/bin/env bash
set -e
cp -a "$BACKUP" "$SSHD"
systemctl restart ssh || service ssh restart || true
echo "Konfigurasi SSH dikembalikan dari $BACKUP"
EOF
chmod +x "$REVERT_SCRIPT"
echo "Jika perlu revert, jalankan: sudo $REVERT_SCRIPT"

# ubah/menambahkan setting di sshd_config
# fungsi bantu: replace atau append jika tidak ada
replace_or_add() {
  local key="$1"; local val="$2"; local file="$3"
  if grep -Eiq "^[#[:space:]]*${key}[[:space:]]" "$file"; then
    sed -ri "s|^[#[:space:]]*(${key}).*|\1 ${val}|I" "$file"
  else
    echo "${key} ${val}" >> "$file"
  fi
}

echo "Mengubah konfigurasi SSH..."
replace_or_add "PermitRootLogin" "yes" "$SSHD"
replace_or_add "PasswordAuthentication" "yes" "$SSHD"
replace_or_add "ChallengeResponseAuthentication" "no" "$SSHD"
# biarkan PubkeyAuthentication tetap ada — supaya key tetap bisa dipakai
replace_or_add "PubkeyAuthentication" "yes" "$SSHD"

# pastikan shell root tidak disable
if passwd -S root 2>/dev/null | grep -q "L"; then
  passwd -u root || true
fi

# set password root
echo "root:${ROOTPW}" | chpasswd
echo "Password root di-set."

# buat fallback user (jika perlu) dan tambahkan ke sudo
if [ "$USE_FALLBACK" = true ]; then
  useradd -m -s /bin/bash "$FALLBACK_USER" || true
  echo "${FALLBACK_USER}:${ROOTPW}" | chpasswd
  # tambahkan ke sudoers jika ada grup sudo/wheel
  if getent group sudo >/dev/null 2>&1; then
    usermod -aG sudo "$FALLBACK_USER" || true
  elif getent group wheel >/dev/null 2>&1; then
    usermod -aG wheel "$FALLBACK_USER" || true
  else
    echo "Tidak menemukan grup sudo/wheel; fallback user mungkin tidak punya sudo."
  fi
  echo "Fallback user '${FALLBACK_USER}' dibuat dengan password yang sama seperti root."
  echo "Login test: ssh ${FALLBACK_USER}@<IP-VPS>"
fi

# restart ssh dengan deteksi systemctl/service
echo "Mere-start layanan SSH..."
if command -v systemctl >/dev/null 2>&1; then
  systemctl restart ssh || systemctl restart sshd || true
else
  service ssh restart || service sshd restart || true
fi

echo
echo "Selesai. Sekarang kamu seharusnya bisa login sebagai root via:"
echo "  ssh root@IP-VPS"
echo
echo "Catatan penting:"
echo " - Jangan tutup sesi SSH yang sedang aktif sampai kamu berhasil login root di sesi baru."
echo " - Jika terjadi masalah, jalankan revert: sudo $REVERT_SCRIPT"
echo " - Setelah berhasil, pertimbangkan untuk menonaktifkan Login root via password untuk keamanan:"
echo "     sudo sed -ri 's|^PermitRootLogin.*|PermitRootLogin prohibit-password|' $SSHD && sudo systemctl restart ssh || sudo service ssh restart"

Просчитайте
стоимость хранения

Нажимая на кнопку, вы соглашаетесь
с политикой конфиденциальности сайта
о компании

Ответственное хранение

logixPRO предлагает не просто услуги ответственного хранения, а складскую логистику высшего уровня в Московской области. Качественный сервис от профессиональной команды. Все условия для хранения, обработки и отгрузки любых товарных групп со склада в оптимальном режиме. Современные склады рядом с Москвой, на самых актуальных направлениях. Мы работаем с максимальной ответственностью и точно в срок по разумным тарифам.

Подробнее о нас

3 причины работать с нами

Опытные специалисты

Опыт работы ключевых сотрудников logixPRO не менее 15 лет. Мы участвовали в развитии складской логистики как услуги в России с ее истоков. В профессиональном портфеле наших ключевых сотрудников запуск и управление складскими комплексам (10 000 – 60 000 м2), открытие распределительного центра, управление складом клиента.

Широкий спектр услуг

У нас есть возможности для изменения конфигурации склада под тип хранения вашего товара. Работает гибкая система резервирования объемов. logixPRO выполнит упаковочные работы - упаковка, стикеровка, термоупаковка, формирование метро-юнитов, подготовка заказов с учетом требований сетей и другие дополнительные услуги.

Теплые склады класса «А»

Складские комплексы logixPRO дают гарантию безопасного и надежного хранения. Удобные подъезды и площадка обеспечивают комфортное передвижение автопоездов. Также к вашим услугам офисные помещения, которые совмещены со складом, система охранной сигнализации, выделенный Интернет, охранное видеонаблюдение и центральное кондиционирование.

кому подойдёт ответственное хранение

Сезонным бизнесам

Бизнесы с ярко-выраженной сезонностью предполагают резкие скачи в потребности площадей для хранения и количества персонала. Как профессиональный складской оператор logixPRO обладает необходимым ресурсом и гибкостью, чтобы обеспечить смену сезонов с минимально-возможными затратами.

Интернет магазинам

Интернет-торговля предполагает высокую интенсивность операций с товаром на складе. Позвольте себе сосредоточится на продажах, пока мы быстро и четко формируем заказы к отправке

Дистрибьютерам

Дистрибьютеры используют услугу ответственного хранения, чтобы оптимизировать логистические процессы. logixPRO обладает достаточным опытом, чтобы улучшить управление запасами и снизить затраты на складирование.
